{
  "signal_description": "Retrieve the following information from the 'defaultview-225' table: 'Inv. Company Code Text', 'Invoice Amount in $', 'No. of Invoices', 'Ø Payment Block Rate in %', 'Ø days posting to due date', 'Automatic Invoice Posting in %', 'Rework Rate in %', 'Change Rate in %'.

To calculate 'Invoice Amount in $', sum the values in the 'Inv. Converted USD Amount' column. To calculate 'No. of Invoices', count the number of values in the 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' column. To calculate 'Ø Payment Block Rate in %', calculate the average of the 'Payment Block Rate' column. To calculate 'Ø days posting to due date', calculate the average difference between the 'Last Inv. Item Due Date' and 'Inv. Posting Document Date' columns. To calculate 'Automatic Invoice Posting in %', count the number of values in the 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' column where 'Event Created By User Type' matches 'System' and 'event_name' matches 'Create Invoice', and divide it by the total count of values in the 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' column. To calculate 'Rework Rate in %', count the number of values in the 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' column where the occurrence of 'event_name' is greater than 1, and divide it by the total count of values in the 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' column, then multiply by 100. To calculate 'Change Rate in %', count the number of values in the 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' column where 'event_name' matches '%update%', and divide it by the total count of values in the 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' column, then multiply by 100. To calculate 'Late Payment Rate in %', count the number of values in the 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' column where 'Last Inv. Item Due Date' is less than 'Last Inv. Item Clearing Date', and divide it by the total count of values in the 'Inv. Accounting Document Number' column where 'Last Inv. Item Clearing Date' is not null, then multiply by 100.

Group the results by 'Inv. Company Code Text' and order them in descending order based on 'Invoice Amount in $'."
}
